[1] Cholera - Burundi (Northwest)
Date: Fri 22 Jul 2005
From: Shirley Bannatyne <shirley.bannatyne@masta.org>
Source: Bonesha FM, Bujumbura, in French [translated by submitter, edited]

Burundi: Cholera epidemic reported in northwest
-----------------------------------------------
A cholera epidemic has been reported in Cibitoke, in the northwestern
part of the country. 20 cases have been reported at the local
hospital. They include soldiers. The disease is caused by lack of
hygiene caused by lack of water.
--
Shirley Bannatyne
MASTA (Medical Advisory Service for Travellers Abroad)
<shirley.bannatyne@masta.org>
