[3] Cholera - Uganda (Kotido)
Date: Mon 25 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: People's Daily Online [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200507/25/eng20050725_197988.html>

Cholera outbreaks in northeastern Uganda
-----------------------------------------------
There has been an outbreak of cholera in Kotido district in
northeastern Uganda, according to a report from Radio Uganda on Sun
24 Jul 2005. The area member of parliament, Rex Achilla, told
government radio that the most hit sub-county is Panyangira, where 3
people have already died.
Rex Achilla said the number of patients being admitted has
overwhelmed health centers. He appealed to the Minister of Health,
Jim Muhwezi, to intervene by sending more medical equipment and
medicine to the district. The MP also advised local people to avoid
drinking un-boiled water.
Last week [3rd week July 2005], the WHO sent health experts to study
the cholera outbreak in Uganda's northwestern district of Arua, where
over 20 people had been killed by the water-borne disease since 16
Jun 2005. In a similar development, over 10 people have been killed
since June 2005 in the Katanga slum, a suburb of Kampala.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
