[4] Cholera - Uganda (Arua, Nebbi)
Date: Tue 26 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200507251627.html>

Cholera Hits Sudan Camp
---------------------------
After a week of calm, the cholera epidemic has resurged in Arua
district, with new cases reported from a Sudanese refugee settlement
in the upper areas of Madi-Okollo county. A man has been killed, and
5 others are said to have contracted the disease mid last week [3rd
week July 2005].
Subsequently, an 8-member team of Arua district officials, led by the
Deputy Resident District Commissioner, Mr. Henry Ringakech, on Sat 23
Jul 2005, closed 4 primary and secondary schools and a market in the
camp.
Meanwhile, 2 new infections have also been confirmed in the outlying
Offaka sub-county, which borders with Nebbi town council, where 2
cholera cases were reportedly admitted within the last 24 hours.
According to medical sources, sporadic outbreaks of cholera have been
reported in Nebbi town council and Wadelai landing site in the past 2
weeks, raising fears that fishmongers from Arua, who frequent the
bay, could contract and spread the disease further in the district.
[Byline: Tabu Butagira]
--
