[6] Cholera - Iran (Qom)
Date: Tue 2 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Iran Focus [edited]
<http://www.iranfocus.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=3122>

Outbreak of cholera in Iran reported
---------------------------------------
At least 3 people have been killed and several others hospitalized
following an outbreak of cholera in the city of Qom, a government-run
website reported on Tue 2 Aug 2005.
The website Baztab, citing unofficial reports, said that, on Mon 1
Aug 2005, authorities quickly moved to close all the sources of water
in various locations throughout Qom.
Officials from the Health Ministry and several health experts had
surmised that the main cause for the new outbreak of the cholera
disease was contaminated water reservoirs. The authorities in Qom
have now warned residents of the threats posed to them.
The last reported outbreak of cholera in Iran was in 1996.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
