[8] Cholera - India (Karnataka)
Date: Mon 25 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: NewIndPress.com [edited]
<http://www.newindpress.com/NewsItems.asp?ID=IEK20050725015454&Page=K&Title=Southern+News+-+Karnataka&Topic=0>

3 die of cholera
----------------
3 cholera deaths were reported in Gulbarga district. As many as 15
persons are suffering from gastritis in Bhusanir village, in Alanda.
Chittapur, Afzalpur and several villages along the Bhima river are in
the grip of cholera. Following heavy rains, people have been drinking
contaminated water.
--
